Diagram 2 (Black's Wish)
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}{\f1\fmodern\fprq2\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par Black 1 is played, hoping white will respond at W2. Then, black cuts at 3 and white dies!
\par
\par \pard\nowidctlpar\qj Next, if white plays at \b\f1 A\b0\f0 , black plays \b\f1 B \b0\f0 and that's it.
\par
\par \pard However, as the previous diagram demonstrates, white will not play in this way.
\par }
